I have had problems using rewrite in this way.  The URL that rewrite analyses may have already been changed by `index` or some other command, and this will lead to redirect loops.  To avoid that problem, I have used:<p><pre><code>    if ($request_uri ~* &quot;^(.*)\.html?$&quot;) {
        return 301 $1;
    }
</code></pre>
The above is a safe use of &quot;if&quot;, and can be helpful since it operates on the actual uri, not the internal uri.
